1. Database Commands  
 
 View all databases  
show dbs  
 Create a new or switch databases 
use 235f9
 View current database  
db  
 Delete current database  
db.dropDatabase() 
   

2. Collection Commands  
  
 Show collections  
  show collections  
 Create a collection named 'students' 
  db.createCollection('comments') 
 Drop a collection named 'students'  
  db.students.drop()


3. Document (Row) Commands  
  
 Show all documents in a collection  
  db.students.find()  
 Show all documents (pretty format)  
  db.students.find().pretty()  
 Find the first document matching a filter  
  db.students.findOne({name: “Prani”})  
 Insert one document  
  db.students.insertOne({name:"Prani",lang:"Java",member_since:6}) 
 Insert many documents  
  db.students.insertMany([  
  {name: 'Sun', lang: 'JavaScript', member_since: 3},  
  {name: 'Mon', lang: 'Python', member_since: 3},  
  {name: 'Tues', lang: 'Java', member_since: 4}  
  ]) 
 Search by field  
  db.students.find({lang: 'Python'})  
 Limit the number of results  
  db.students.find().limit(2)  
 Skip results (useful for pagination)  
  db.students.find().skip(2).limit(2)  
 Count the number of matching documents  
  db.students.countDocuments({lang: 'Python'})


4. Update Commands  
  
 Update one document  
  db.students.updateOne(  
               {name: 'Wed'},  
   {$set: {name: ‘Prani', lang: 'Java', member_since: 3}},  
   {upsert: true}  
  )  
 Update many documents  
  db.students.updateMany(  
   {lang: 'JavaScript'},  
   {$set: {verified: true}}  
  )  
 Increment a field 
db.students.updateOne(  
   {name: 'Sun'},  
   {$inc: {member_since: 2}}  
  )  
 Rename a field  
  db.students.updateOne(  
   {name: 'Sun'},  
   {$rename: {member_since: 'member'}}  
  )


5. Delete Commands  
 
 Delete one document  
  db.students.deleteOne({name: 'Prani’})  
 Delete many documents  
  db.students.deleteMany({lang: ‘Java’})
